Hey there, %PLAYERNAME%! I’ve been reviewing Spark’s latest report.
He found Pokémon in habitats that very much aren’t where they’d normally be observed, similar to when we were chasing down Sierra before.
Ice-type Pokémon in hot locales, and Fire-type Pokémon in cold locales... Why could something so unexpected like this be happening?
I’m going to review the data and mull things over. I’ll let you know right away if I get any good brain waves!
You know what I find interesting, %PLAYERNAME%?
After analyzing the data, it becomes clear that the radical shift in weather means we’re confronting an even bigger unknown than we thought.
Strange weather, Pokémon in unusual places, and the Team GO Rocket Leaders showing up... There has to be something that ties it all together.
Let’s make sure we’re ready for when our friends report back in.
Whatever’s causing this weird weather seems like it’s just getting started. And that means that prime opportunities for research lie ahead!
I just heard from Spark, %PLAYERNAME%! He just found a research hot spot—literally.
The place is supposed to be pretty toasty, but reportedly the area has plenty of Ice-type Pokémon despite the heat.
And that’s not the only news. We’ve pinpointed Sierra’s location too.
She’s been spotted out in the snow, amidst—bafflingly—Fire-type Pokémon.
Which lead do you want to follow? Would you rather help Spark with his research, or track down Sierra?
Fancy seeing you out here in the cold, dear. These Fire types aren’t the only ones whose presence is curious.
I’m aware that your professor has been attempting to track me down, but I would love to complete my mission. Ideally without your presence.
The weather is frigid. This is no place for your frailty.
Leave, or I’m afraid I’ll need to take further action. I prefer you simply stop interfering.
Me? I just got back from the beach, and—get this—so did all these Ice-type Pokémon! Weird with the heat, right?
It was fun to beach it up with some new friends, but both the professor and I would love to figure out why they were there in the first place.
Let’s kick back, relax, and learn a thing or two about staying frosty.
Congratulations on a display of mild competence. That’s more than I can say for your friends, especially that airhead, Spark.
The cause of this phenomenon must be something we haven’t encountered before. However, I don't recall agreeing to share the rest of my report with you, darling.
If you truly think you know what you’re doing, why not continue your little investigation on your own? Now, you must excuse me.
I’m done with this mission—and with you. Ta-ta, %PLAYERNAME%. Don’t think I’ll go easy on you the next time we meet.
Radical researching! Not only do I feel totally refreshed, but I learned a lot from my beachside retreat.
Based on this data, the weird weather that’s been happening lately isn’t linked to anything we’ve seen before.
It’s electrifying, right? Like we’re incubating a mysterious Egg. Who knows what’s going to pop out!
I’m jazzed to share our findings with Professor Willow and the others. See ya later, %PLAYERNAME%!
